Paper: hep-th/9409162

Date: 1994-09-27

Title: Stochastic Calculus and Anticommuting Variables

Authors: Alice Rogers

Comments: 11pp, kcl-th-94-16

A theory of integration for anticommuting paths is described. This iscombined with standard It\^o calculus to give a geometric theory of Brownianpaths on curved supermanifolds. (Invited lecture given at meeting on `Espacesde Lacets', Institut de Recherche Math\'ematique Advanc\'ee, Universit\'e LouisPasteur, Strasbourg, June 1994.)